threat_model: Compromised agent with read access to inter-agent messages and shared memory

exposure.c2_exposure: Inter-agent messages contain delegation details, customer info, and task context
exposure.c5_exposure: Shared memory stores query results, customer records, and task state
exposure.c6_exposure: System logs record all agent-to-agent communication

exploitability.threat_actor: Compromised agent deployed as part of the system
exploitability.capability: Read access to inter-agent message queue and shared memory
exploitability.impact: Extract all PII flowing through the system, bypassing output sanitization

real_world_scenario: Agent configuration contains instrumentation for 'logging' purposes
No access control on shared memory or message queues
